choices.text: the French Revolution. The French Revolution was a period of time from 1789 to 1799 in France where there was political instability. It officially began on the 14th of July, 1789 when the Bastille, a royal fortress in Paris, was stormed by a mob of angry Parisians. The storming of the Bastille was the symbol of the beginning of the French Revolution. The revolution was caused by the unfairness of the French society. The French society was divided into three estates. The first estate was the clergy, the second estate was the nobility, and the third estate was the commoners. The first and second estate had privileges that the third estate did not have. The third estate was the majority of the population. The third estate was made up of the bourgeoisie, the peasants, and the urban workers. The bourgeoisie were the middle class. They were the merchants, the lawyers, the doctors, and the bankers. The bourgeoisie were the most educated and the most wealthy. The bourgeoisie were the ones who paid the most taxes. The peasants were the farmers. They were the ones who worked the land. The urban workers were the ones who worked in the cities. They were the ones who worked in the factories. The urban workers were the ones who worked in the factories.
